overview: D is an unemployed clinical social worker, who is attempting to get her certification as a hypnotherapist through Wellness Institute. She has been looking for work but is thus far unsuccessful. She is a disabled veteran of the Air Force, where she met her husband of 34 yrs, who is retired now. In the course of their service, they have lived in CA, HI, MD, TX, & the Republic of Korea. They are living his dream! The view includes: amber waves of grain, wind 365 days a year, antelope, coyotes, owls, golden & bald eagles, fox, & a 300-mile stretch of mountains. They have a small home on the high plains, in central USA where their nearest neighbor is approximately Â½ mile close. They live w/their 4 furry family members: 4 y/o blue great dane bitch & 2 2-y/o male & 1 female cats. She & her husband are thinking of bringing in a new male puppy but as yet haven’t decided on a breed. They are committed to matching w/a breed that will fit into their lifestyle. Some of her favourite things: reading, playing w/their furry family members, writing novels, & travelling – so long as she can come back home, where the 6 of them are living their dream! She loves to talk to people of all shapes, sizes, colors – even the purple polka dotteds!
